POSITION:


As a Financial Business Analyst, you’ll partner closely with the CFO to improve the company’s profitability by analyzing its finances and business model. Your duties include reviewing company budgets, making recommendations, and helping to refine operations and increase efficiency. Ideal skills include understanding how finances impact business operations and using your judgment to make recommendations for reducing costs, generating more revenue, and improving financial reporting. Collaborating with management and other strategic partners, the Financial Business Analyst facilitates an understanding of the business dynamics which includes productivity analysis, margin improvement, and business analysis. The role is responsible for conducting financial analysis and data mining to develop KPIs to measure financial and operational performance to assist business planning and improve reporting accuracy and operational efficiency.


POSITION DESCRIPTION:

Create financial models to develop the annual operating plan, reviewing and validating assumptions, ensuring proper reconciliation and data integrity;
Build forecast models using key drivers, trend analysis, and monitor the accuracy of models;
Improve forecast accuracy by aligning to key drivers and identifying opportunities for improvement;
Code new and existing employees in NetSuite;
Assist is reporting metrics; streamline monthly reporting processes;
Work with segment leaders on metrics reporting, and new dashboards;
Create a monthly process for allocations across business units/segments;
Drive rolling monthly forecast and short/long-term planning;
Build working relationships with business management and other partners in support of key priorities and objectives through complex analytics and insights;
Ad-hoc analysis for segment leaders;
Partner with the CFO on monthly operating review packages.


QUALIFICATIONS:

Bachelor's Degree in Business, Economics, Accounting, or equivalent;
Four-plus years of financial analysis experience;
Experience managing financials with business partners;
Experience problem-solving independently, organizing workload and priorities, and completing tasks on time;
Experience with NetSuite or similar ERP systems.


PREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS:

Experience in financial planning and creating data-driven analysis;
Experience managing monthly and quarterly reporting cycles.

