Bank, NJ. Blueshift maintains a high-turnover equity market neutral strategy that leverages the firm’s core
experience in systematic investing. It is comprised of a combination of multiple statistical arbitrage and
high-frequency trading strategies. We are currently seeking an extremely bright, articulate, highly
motivated candidate to join our Business Operations Team.

Responsibilities will impact a variety of the management company (“the Firm”) and investment vehicles’
(“the Funds”) operations and initiatives, including:

Assist in maintaining the Firm’s books and records, including the reconciliation and
monitoring of payables and receivables;

Assist with managing service provider relationships for the Firm, its offices, and Funds;
Assist in the daily reconciliation of trading activities;
Assist in reviewing and calculating the monthly net asset value for the Funds;
Assist with annual financial statements, audit process, and related tax statement
preparation for the Firm and Funds;

Assistance in the preparation of regulatory filings, as needed;
Participate in ad-hoc requests and special projects that involve other groups including
compliance, technology, and investor relations.

Education and Experience Requirements:

CPA license is preferred;
2-5 years of relevant work experience; experience in the alternatives industry is not
required;

Experience across accounting, audit, and tax is beneficial;
Experience with QuickBooks;
Advanced experience with Excel;
Unix experience is a strong plus, but not essential;
Interpersonal skills and ability to communicate effectively are essential.

We offer the following:

Competitive compensation and benefits, with tremendous long-term earnings potential;
Ability to interact with highly talented and experienced professionals in a casual yet
academic environment;

Ability to join a rapidly growing firm and have an outsized impact;
Ample cultural and recreational activities, with nearby access to New York City,
Philadelphia, and the Jersey Shore.
